{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 03:21:36.827063", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report — SDN Spine–Leaf Lab\\n\\nSummary of current health\\n- End-to-end and intra-leaf L2 connectivity in the 10.0.0.0/24 host subnet is non-functional. Hosts cannot reach each other, including pairs attached to the same leaf.\\n- All OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are connected to the SDN controller at 20.0.0.100:6633 and report all data-plane ports as LIVE.\\n- Flow tables are populated with non-learning, highly specific rules that do not support ARP/broadcast or unknown unicast. Some rules appear to “hairpin” frames back to the ingress port. There is no table-miss behavior to the controller.\\n- Result: ARP resolution fails, leading to ICMP “Destination Host Unreachable” and timeouts.\\n\\nKey test evidence\\n- Reachability:\\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2 (same leaf_2): Destination Host Unreachable (from 10.0.0.9) for all probes.\\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2 and host_1_1 -> host_2_1: ping commands time out.\\n- Host IP configs: All hosts correctly configured in 10.0.0.0/24 with direct-connected routes. No default gateways involved; expect pure L2 bridging across the fabric.\\n- OVS/controller state:\\n  - leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" is_connected: true; fail_mode: secure.\\n  - All relevant physical ports report state LIVE at 10Gb, indicating links are up.\\n  - openvswitch-switch systemd service shows inactive (dead), yet OVS is clearly active and responding (bridge present, ofctl working), so systemd state is not blocking the dataplane here.\\n- Flow tables (selected observations):\\n  - leaf_1: a rule in_port=1 actions=output:1 (hairpin on access port eth0). No learning/flooding rules. Other rules match unknown MAC pairs (e.g., be:77:..., 5e:ba:...) that do not correspond to host MACs in this lab.\\n  - leaf_2: similar pattern; in_port=2 actions=output:2 and several rules with unexpected MACs. A few rules reference the MACs of host_1_2 (c6:e7:52:c2:d6:44) and host_2_1 (e2:e1:d5:19:eb:59), but there is no general ARP/unknown-unicast handling.\\n  - spine_1: numerous highly specific dl_src/dl_dst rules; no broadcast/unknown handling path.\\n  - No table-miss entries directing unknown traffic to the controller or a learning pipeline; miss_send_len=0 and no evidence of a table-miss flow. In OpenFlow 1.3, absence of a table-miss entry results in drop.\\n\\nAbnormal behaviors identified\\n- L2 reachability failure even between hosts on the same leaf, which should work with basic L2 switching.\\n- Flow tables lack:\\n  - ARP broadcast flooding.\\n  - Unknown unicast flooding or learning behavior.\\n  - Table-miss entries to send unmatched frames to the controller for reactive programming.\\n- Presence of “hairpin” rules (in_port=N output:N) on access ports effectively keeps frames on the ingress port, preventing any forwarding across the fabric.\\n- Installed MAC-specific flows reference MAC addresses not present on the actual hosts (e.g., 5e:ba:a1:57:b4:5c, be:77:b4:2d:76:66), suggesting stale or incorrect controller intent.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Data plane devices: leaf_1, leaf_2, and spine_1 OpenFlow pipelines (flow tables) are misprogrammed, causing drops of ARP and unknown unicast and preventing intra/inter-leaf forwarding.\\n- Control plane: SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 is connected and actively programming flows, but the flows are inappropriate for this topology and host set.\\n\\nLikely root cause\\n- Controller misconfiguration or a mismatched application/policy is installing incorrect and incomplete OpenFlow rules:\\n  - Hairpin-only per-port rules on leaf access ports.\\n  - Numerous dl_src/dl_dst-specific entries for MACs not belonging to the current hosts.\\n  - No table-miss to the controller, no ARP/unknown flooding, and no learning behavior.\\n- With fail_mode set to secure, any traffic not matching these incorrect rules is dropped silently, leading to a complete L2 outage across the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet.\\n\\nImpact scope\\n- All hosts in the 10.0.0.0/24 segment are affected. No east–west host connectivity is currently possible, including within a single leaf.\\n\\nNotes\\n- Although the openvswitch-switch systemd service reports inactive, OVS daemons are operational (bridges exist, ofctl and vsctl commands succeed, controller sessions are live). The outage is attributable to the flow programming, not to OVS process liveness or link state., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c0a8e36c-040a-4c9d-99dd-f9ddb4886e9c'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
